It is important to understand that the spot #Bitcoin ETFs have a window of time or lag between when they receive cash (funds) and when they can purchase actual #btc with those funds. In some cases, the SEC may allow via waiver an ETF up to 6 months leeway between receipt of funds and purchase of the underlying asset, depending on a variety of factors, such as asset availability. We know #Bitcoin is incredibly scarce so this could be an issue if demand were to explode beyond what's being anticipated. 

While this 6 month leeway in the form of a waiver is rather rare and would be incredibly dangerous for #Bitcoin ETFs to play with given BTC's 80 vol nature, I will be watching the 5 pm ET (NY time) very closely over the next few weeks. I want to monitor what spot prices do in the period leading up to 5 pm (the typical cut off) and after. ü§î Help me monitor this if you can as well. The more eyes the better. 
#stackharder

Since starting at Swan a few weeks ago, one thing is becoming abundantly clear. A LOT of Americans are planning to retire on #Bitcoin. 

Most of the high net worth clients, unsurprisingly, are either Gen-X (my generation) or Boomers. That much was expected. What I didn't expect was the quantity of people with IRAs who are keen on hodling REAL BTC in their retirement accounts! 

They are coming in droves every single day, and they are already convicted about Bitcoin because of the quality and quantity of Bitcoin-focused content out there. 

Most are NOT on crypto Twitter, but they ARE on YouTube, paying close attention to folks like @LynAldenContact, and many have watched @Breedlove22's What is Money Show and @PeterMcCormack's What Bitcoin Did. 

America is being orange-pilled at a level that most people are wholly unaware of. 

We are winning the race to avoid the war. Once enough people (3%-4% of Americans) hold BTC in their retirement accounts, it will become extremely unpopular to talk about banning self-custody. Getting BTC into retirement accounts is how we defeat people like @SenWarren because it'll be political suicide to even bring up banning people from holding their own keys.

For weeks now I have been talking about how data is short-term overheated for #Bitcoin, and that still hasn't changed.

This is despite the small move above 45k.

Time frames to the mid-top have been no more than 6 days after crossing the red 2 LTH MVRV value line.

We are now a month out!

Corrective periods are just a part of the cycle.

Some people say that a 30% correction is ridiculous, but it's entirely plausible based on how much price has risen with no real pullback.

I'm a messenger for the data, and this is what it tells us. You can argue with it at your own risk!

It's time to adapt to the price action!

#Bitcoin has now reached 47k, well surpassing my previous expectations that 45k was a local high.

I had that idea due to a multitude of data in favor it.

So then, is this time different?

Not yet.

You can say that after all data hits its mark and Bitcoin still decides it's not time to correct.

The MVRV-Z and some other data still has room for increase to the red zone, and it now seems very likely that it will be achieved.

This would mean there is room for higher prices above even 47k if true.

The .618 cycle retrace lies at about 48.5k, which has marked every cycle mid-top.

It seems to be all much more simple than I anticipated.

I will continue to navigate price with the long-term data just as I always have using logical thinking.

I simply wait to see what comes of the ETF speculation and do not try and anticipate it.

#Bitcoin is not prepared for new ATHs in the near future.

This comes after crossing above the CCI Critical Zone.

Instead, it formed a pinnacle inside it just like we've seen from 4 other examples before a near 30% decline.

This triggered at 45k in December 2023, even though price has gone slightly higher I think this is only prolonging the inevitable cool-down.

These cooldowns can take many months to resolve.

The ETF speculation window is almost over, and price may be holding on to see how that transpires.

Whatever the outcome of that new event, data has made its position clear.

Cycles are right on track.
